"""
api.py - FastAPI Backend for NeuraVault

This module creates the REST API backend for the NeuraVault RAG application.
Replaces the Chainlit UI with API endpoints consumed by a Next.js frontend.

Security Best Practices implemented:
    ✔ Rate Limiting          - slowapi per-IP throttling
    ✔ Authentication         - JWT bearer tokens (register / login / refresh)
    ✔ Authorization          - role-based access control (admin / user)
    ✔ Input Validation       - strict Pydantic models with sanitisation
    ✔ CORS Configuration     - explicit origin allowlist, no wildcard
    ✔ Security Headers       - OWASP headers via middleware
    ✔ SQL Injection Prev.    - parameterized queries in database.py
    ✔ XSS Prevention         - input/output sanitisation + CSP header
    ✔ CSRF Protection        - double-submit cookie middleware
    ✔ Password Hashing       - bcrypt via passlib

Endpoints:
    Auth:
        POST /api/auth/register   — Create a new user account
        POST /api/auth/login      — Authenticate & receive tokens
        POST /api/auth/refresh    — Refresh an access token
        GET  /api/auth/me         — Current user profile

    Protected (require Bearer token):
        POST /api/query           — Process a question through the RAG engine
        POST /api/upload          — Upload PDF files for ingestion
        POST /api/ingest          — Trigger vector-DB ingestion
        GET  /api/documents       — List uploaded documents

    Public:
        GET  /api/health          — Health / readiness check
        GET  /api/starters        — Starter question suggestions
        GET  /api/csrf-token      — Obtain a fresh CSRF token

Run with: uvicorn neuravault.api:app --reload
"""

